msgSnippet: You need to change the errors settings in Window  Preferences  Java  Compiler (or somewhere in that region).  This also seems to be the problem indicated in
messageBody:
You need to change the errors settings in Window > Preferences > Java >
Compiler (or somewhere in that region). This also seems to be the
problem indicated in your previous post. They aren't real compilation
errors. They are artificial errors to help you code better (don't allow
unneeded imports, unused variables/methods, etc.). They are all
configurable, just turn them off if you don't like them (set the option
to 'ignore').

=jason
